{
  "texts": [
    "Our approach integrates Bangla text and image data by a single multimodal deep learning pipeline as in Figure 2.",
    "The framework consists of four main components: data preprocessing, feature extraction, early fusion, and classification.",
    "The architectural choices were motivated by computational efficiency requirements for real-time disaster response and proven effectiveness in low-resource language scenarios.",
    "We selected BanglaBERT for native Bangla understanding, mBERT for multilingual robustness, and XLM-RoBERTa for superior cross-lingual transfer learning capabilities [16].",
    "ResNet50, DenseNet169, and MobileNetV2 were chosen over Vision Transformers for computational efficiency in real-time disaster scenarios [10]."
  ]
}